The paper deals with the concept of Kolmogorov complexity, which is a fundamental concept in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the study of complexity of pairs, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The additivity theorem proved in the paper has applications in computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves the study of plain conditional complexities, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
